added.title: The Signature
added.description: Dad discovers that Granny Jojo and Louie are planning to get married and move to Florida. To stop this happening he adopts Louie so that he can forbid him from marrying Granny Jojo. But this triggers a series of adoptions within the family which quickly spirals out of control, and causes the unexpected return of someone from Dad's past.

added.title: The Routine
added.description: Mom and the kids depart for their hard day's work, leaving a seemingly lazy Dad half-asleep on the sofa. Mom has given him one very simple job: buy mayonnaise. However, Dad manages to turn this mundane task into an epic quest, showing that his daily routine isn't as inactive as his family imagine.

added.title: The Joy
added.description: Miss Simian has to save herself from a contagious Joy virus infecting the whole school. After Dad gives Gumball and Darwin a special hug, the kids go to school filled with a virulent form of Joy. Miss Simian quickly identifies the terrible affliction, and soon enough it spreads to the other kids. She has to find a cure before it's too late. Before Ms Simian herself is won over by . . . Joy.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Name
added.description: When Gumball discovers his real name is Zach...he starts acting like one! When Mom reveals that Gumball's real name is "Zach", Gumball adopts a cheesy, annoying persona to match the name.  His family try to make him remember the old Gumball, as this new Zach persona is progressively taking over Gumball's life and erasing his memories. If they can't reach him in time, the old Gumball will disappear forever and they'll be left with...Zach!

added.title: The Fraud
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover Principal Brown's diploma is a fake. When Gumball and Darwin discover his diploma is fake, Principal Brown is determined to keep their discovery a secret. He offers them all sorts of "incentives" to keep quiet but the truth is they really don't care whether the diploma is real or not. Mistaking their disinterest as "playing hard to get" Principal Brown resorts to increasingly desperate measures to ensure Gumball and Darin play ball.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Watch
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

added.title: The Bumpkin
added.description: Envious of his rustic lifestyle, Gumball invites Idaho over to teach the Wattersons how to live like a potato.

added.title: The Photo
added.description: It's school picture day and Gumball has until 3pm to take one good photo - or have his legacy ruined forever.

added.title: The Storm
added.description: Love is in the air and Gumball is caught in the center of an emotional hurricane - literally!

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Prank
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's harmless pranks on Dad spiral hopelessly out of control.

added.title: The Party
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are invited to a high school party, and have to bring a date!

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Rooms
added.description: The Bears switch bedrooms for the night and get a glimpse of the living space of one of their brothers. But the deeper they go, hidden secrets are revealed.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Last One Out of Beach City
added.description: Pearl, Steven and Amethyst go to a rock show.

added.title: Onion Gang
added.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

added.title: Steven's Dream
added.description: A strange dream prompts Steven to search for answers.

added.title: Adventures in Light Distortion
added.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

added.title: Log Date 7 15 2
added.description: Steven sneaks a listen to a friend's audio diary.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: The New Lars
added.description: Steven gets a new look into Lars' life.

added.title: Monster Reunion
added.description: Steven reunites with an old friend.

added.title: Alone at Sea
added.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

added.title: Monster Buddies
added.description: Steven accidentally releases a monster from a gem bubble and attempts to tame its wild, violent instincts.

added.title: Mirror Gem
added.description: Steven befriends a magical mirror that can mysteriously communicate with him.

added.title: Fusion Cuisine
added.description: In an effort to win over Connie's parents, Steven convinces the Gems to fuse together and pretend to be his mother.

added.title: Watermelon Steven
added.description: Steven discovers a new power when he grows a patch of Steven-shaped watermelons!

added.title: Future Vision
added.description: Steven learns that Garnet can see into the future and becomes curious about the possible dangers that lurk around him.

added.title: Horror Club
added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

removed.title: Winter Forecast
removed.description: Steven has to get Connie home before it snows.

removed.title: Rising Tides/Crashing Skies
removed.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

removed.title: Beta
removed.description: Steven and Amethyst visit some friends in the country but Amethyst isn't being herself.

removed.title: Warp Tour
removed.description: Steven thinks he sees something creepy traversing the warp streams and the Gems try to ease his paranoia.

removed.title: Say Uncle
removed.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

removed.title: On the Run
removed.description: Steven and Amethyst try out life on the road.

removed.title: Sworn to the Sword
removed.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

removed.title: Kiki's Pizza Delivery Service
removed.description: Steven saves Kiki from some delicious nightmares.

removed.title: I Am My Mom
removed.description: Steven struggles to fix his mistakes.

removed.title: Steven vs. Amethyst
removed.description: Steven and Amethyst get competitive while training with Pearl.

removed.title: Bear Flu
removed.description: The Bears become terribly ill and Chloe takes it upon herself to take care of them. But things get tricky when word of the Bears' sickness goes viral.

removed.title: Burrito
removed.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

removed.title: Pet Shop
removed.description: Pet Shop tells the tale of where the Baby Bears once lived, and after a run-in with a video crew shooting a Sarah McLachlan-type animal adoption video, almost seized an opportunity to find a home separated from each other.

removed.title: The Road
removed.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

removed.title: Everyday Bears
removed.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

removed.title: The Audition
removed.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

removed.title: Food Truck
removed.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

removed.title: The Crew
removed.description: When Gumball and Darwin decide it's time they join a crew, they agree that the coolest posse in Elmore is the Senior Citizens. They do everything they can to fit in with them, going to extraordinary lengths to prove themselves worthy of running (well, walking very slowly) with them.

removed.title: The Return
removed.description: Dad is in charge of getting the kids to their first day back at school on time, but he's overslept and now he can't find Gumball, Darwin or Anais anywhere. He sets about retracing his steps from the day before to work out where they might be.

removed.title: The Ape
removed.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

removed.title: The Kids
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's voices may be breaking, but they're showing no signs of growing up. Whilst Gumball and Darwin make fun of Mom and Dad for being old, their voices start to break. They try to ignore it, but everybody they meet reacts to their new and unpredictable voices. Gumball and Darwin finally decide to make the most of their childhood whilst there's still time.

removed.title: The Remote
removed.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

removed.title: The Fridge
removed.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

removed.title: The Puppy
removed.description: The kids finally get the puppy they always wanted, except . . . it's actually a turtle, and it hates them. After begging Dad for a puppy, the kids are taken aback when he comes home with a turtle. Despite the fact that the turtle turns out to be extremely aggressive (especially toward Gumball) they try their best to give it the love it deserves. This achieves nothing. The Evil Turtle escapes and goes on a rampage, and they have to find it before it destroys Elmore.

removed.title: The Re-Run
removed.description: When we last saw Gumball, he was hitting rewind on Rob's Universal Remote just in time to save himself from being trapped in The Void. The remote has now taken Gumball back to the beginning of that disastrous day. Armed with the knowledge of what this day has in store, he must try and stop Rob from destroying his life.

removed.title: The Genius
removed.description: Darwin is sent away to a government institute for geniuses. Yes. Really.

removed.title: The Scam
removed.description: At Halloween show and tell, the class isn't buying Gumball's story about Gargaroth the Devourer until Carrie fakes a terrifying haunting. The kids convince the school to hire them as ghost exterminators and take their payment in Halloween candy. But when it turns out Gargaroth is real, suddenly Gumball is expected to be the town's savior.
